The post’s numbers are inaccurate, but abortions do far outnumber deaths from COVID-19 and flu.
The COVID-19 number is likely too low, and the flu number is too high.
Flu deaths: The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention estimated there would be 23,000 flu deaths during the 2019-2020 flu season, which began Sept. 29, 2019, according to the latest weekly update from the released March 14, 2020.
Abortions: Abortions are reported on an annual basis.
It’s generally true that the number of abortions in the United States far outpaces the number of deaths to COVID-19 or the flu.